      "message": "Issue #5: Ensure User Exists Creates Side Effects\nLocation: Lines 15-20 in lib/usermanagement_utils.robot\n```\nCurrent Code:\nIF  not ${user_exists}\n    Redfish Create User  ${username}  ${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}  ${role}  ${True}\nEND\n```\n\nIssue: Creates user with hardcoded enabled\u003d${True}, never deletes it, no verification of creation success.\nFix: Add cleanup and verification:\n```\nEnsure User Exists\n    [Arguments]  ${username}  ${role}  ${enabled}\u003d${True}\n    \n    ${user_exists}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n    ...  Redfish.Get  /redfish/v1/AccountService/Accounts/${username}\n    \n    IF  not ${user_exists}\n        Redfish Create User  ${username}  ${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}  ${role}  ${enabled}\n        # Verify creation succeeded\n        ${resp}\u003d  Redfish.Get  /redfish/v1/AccountService/Accounts/${username}\n        Should Be Equal As Strings  ${resp.dict[\u0027Enabled\u0027]}  ${enabled}\n        # Mark for cleanup\n        Set Test Variable  ${USER_CREATED_BY_TEST}  ${username}\n    END\n```\n\nWhy: Prevents test pollution and allows tests to control initial user state.",
