      "message": "Issue #4: Inconsistent Teardown Between Test Cases\nLocation: Lines 283-295 in redfish/managers/test_bmc_protocol_settings.robot\nCurrent Code:\n\n```\n# Line 286 - Disable test HAS teardown\n[Teardown]  Set User Account State  admin_user  ${True}\n\n# Line 295 - Enable test has NO teardown\nEnable Admin User Verify User Is Allowed To Do SSH On SOL Port\n    [Documentation]  Enable admin user and verify user is allowed to login via SSH on SOL port.\n    [Tags]  Enable_Admin_User_Verify_User_Is_Allowed_To_Do_SSH_On_SOL_Port\n    Verify User Enable Disable And SSH Login  admin_user  Administrator  ${HOST_SOL_PORT}  ${True}\n```\n\nIssue: Only the \"Disable\" test has teardown. If \"Enable\" test fails midway, user could be left disabled, affecting subsequent tests.\n\nFix: Add consistent teardown to both tests:\n```\n\nEnable Admin User Verify User Is Allowed To Do SSH On SOL Port\n    [Documentation]  Enable admin user and verify user is allowed to login via SSH on SOL port.\n    [Tags]  Enable_Admin_User_Verify_User_Is_Allowed_To_Do_SSH_On_SOL_Port\n    [Teardown]  Set User Account State  admin_user  ${True}\n    \n    Verify User Enable Disable And SSH Login  admin_user  Administrator  ${HOST_SOL_PORT}  ${True}\n```\n\nWhy: Ensures consistent cleanup and prevents test pollution.",
