      "message": "Issue #2: Multiple Redfish Logins Without Session Management\n```\n# Line 382 in test_bmc_protocol_settings.robot\nRun Keywords  Redfish.Login  AND  Enable SSH Protocol  ${True}\n```\n\nFix Required:\n\n```\n# Option 1: Check if already logged in\n${logged_in}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status  Redfish.Get  /redfish/v1/SessionService/Sessions\nIF  not ${logged_in}\n    Redfish.Login\nEND\nEnable SSH Protocol  ${True}\n\n# Option 2: Remove redundant login (Suite Setup already logs in)\nEnable SSH Protocol  ${True}\n```\n\nWhy: Suite Setup already calls Redfish.Login at line 303. Logging in again without logout creates multiple sessions, potentially exhausting BMC session limits (typically 4-16 concurrent sessions). This could cause test failures or affect other tests.",
