      "message": "Issue #3: No Verification That State Change Took Effect\n```\n# Lines 389-393\nSet User Account State  ${username}  ${False}\nSleep  ${USER_STATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT}\nVerify SSH Login Access  ${username}  ${port}  ${False}\n```\n\nFix Required:\n\n```\nSet User Account State  ${username}  ${False}\n# Verify state actually changed via Redfish\nWait Until Keyword Succeeds  ${USER_STATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT}  2s\n...  Verify User State Via Redfish  ${username}  ${False}\nVerify SSH Login Access  ${username}  ${port}  ${False}\n\n# New keyword needed:\nVerify User State Via Redfish\n    [Arguments]  ${username}  ${expected_enabled}\n    ${resp}\u003d  Redfish.Get  /redfish/v1/AccountService/Accounts/${username}\n    Should Be Equal As Strings  ${resp.dict[\u0027Enabled\u0027]}  ${expected_enabled}\n```\n\nWhy: Fixed sleep assumes state propagates in exactly 10 seconds. If it takes longer, test fails. If it\u0027s faster, we waste time. More critically, we never verify the Redfish PATCH actually worked - BMC could return 200 but fail to apply the change.",
