      "message": "ssue #6: No Verification of SSH Connection Failure Reason\nLocation: Lines 423-431 in redfish/managers/test_bmc_protocol_settings.robot\nCurrent Code:\n```\n${login_status}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n...  Open Connection And Log In  host\u003d${OPENBMC_HOST}  port\u003d${port}\n...  username\u003d${username}  password\u003d${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}\n```\n\nIssue: SSH connection could fail for many reasons (network down, SSH service stopped, wrong port, timeout), not just user disabled. Test would pass/fail for wrong reasons.\nFix: Add pre-checks and better error handling:\n```\n\n# Verify SSH service is running on the port first with a known-good user\n${ssh_service_up}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n...  Open Connection And Log In  host\u003d${OPENBMC_HOST}  port\u003d${port}\n...  username\u003d${OPENBMC_USERNAME}  password\u003d${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}  timeout\u003d5s\nRun Keyword If  ${ssh_service_up}  Close All Connections\nShould Be True  ${ssh_service_up}  msg\u003dSSH service on port ${port} is not accessible\n\n# Now test target user authentication\n${login_status}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n...  Open Connection And Log In  host\u003d${OPENBMC_HOST}  port\u003d${port}\n...  username\u003d${username}  password\u003d${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}  timeout\u003d10s\n```\n\nWhy: Distinguishes between SSH service issues and user authentication issues by first verifying service is up with a known-good account.",
